Description
Write a story covering all the characteristics mentioned in the attached le.
Once you have written the rst draft exchange work with a classmates, make corrections to eachothers work.
Make the corrections.
Be prepared to read your story next class.
The features of the story that you should write are these:
1. 180-200 words
2. 5 paragraphs: Introduction; three main paragraphs with the succession of the events; conclusion.
3. Use of all the past tenses seen in class (you can include any other tense if you need but the past tenses
are mandatory:
a. past simple;
b. past progressive; Was/ Were + ing
c. past perfect; Had + participle
i. The past perfect shows the earlier action and the past simple shows the later action.
d. present perfect; have or has + past participle
i. past actions or states which are still connected to the present.
e. used to.
4. Use of the following resources: linking words; several adjectives to describe places, characters and
situations; direct speech.
5. Use of the phrases provided in the list below. (Useful language).
6. Tell the story in rst or third person.
7. The topic is totally free.
